org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.kubernetes.lifecycle

Class KubernetesLifecycle

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.core.plugin.lifecycle.AbstractLifecycle
      • org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.kubernetes.lifecycle.KubernetesLifecycle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransformationLifecycle, LifecycleAccess

    public final class KubernetesLifecycle
extends AbstractLifecycle
    Implements the Lifecycle Operations for the Kubernetes plugin.

    In order to keep the Filesize (in terms of LOC) small all phases have been put into separate classes (extending the LifecycleHandler. This class just stores the Fields that are commonly used in these phases.

    • Field Detail

      • model

        protected final EffectiveModel model
        The Effective Model (stores the TOSCA topology)

      • nodes

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,KubernetesNodeContainer> nodes
        A Name to Node Map for every node in the topology (Nodes get wrapped in KubernetesNodeContainers)

        This field gets populated with data during the prepare() phase

      • computeNodes

        protected java.util.Set<KubernetesNodeContainer> computeNodes
        A Set of all compute nodes in the topology

        This field gets populated during the prepare() phase

      • stacks

        protected java.util.Set<NodeStack> stacks
        The set of nodeStacks (nodes that will belong into the same container image). the grouping process is done during the prepare() phase

      • pods

        protected java.util.List<Pod> pods
        The list of Pods.

        This list gets created at the end of the prepare() phase (after all NodeStacks have been created) Some of the data will be populated during the transform phase (for example: Open ports) Doing this so early is needed to know the Public and Private addresses for a Compute node (In kubernetes this is represented as as Service)

    • Method Detail

      • checkModel

        public boolean checkModel()
        Description copied from interface: TransformationLifecycle
        Checks if the Model (of the context that has been given during construction) is valid for this plugin That means the model gets checked for invalid properties such as unsupported operating systems or architectures
        Returns:
        True if the validation succeeded, false otherwise. Returning false will cause the transformation to fail

      • prepare

        public void prepare()
        Description copied from interface: TransformationLifecycle
        Has to implement the prepare lifecycle operations

        The Prepare lifecycle phase is described as follows: in this step the plugin processes the graph to transform it in the following step. For example the kubernetes plugin needs to split the graph into container and pods.

        Exceptions have to be handled within the method, The transformation will abort if a runtime exception gets thrown out of the method. To abort the transformation yo have to execute throw new RuntimeException()

      • transform

        public void transform()
        Description copied from interface: TransformationLifecycle
        Has to implement the transform lifecycle operations

        The 'transform' lifecycle phase is described as follows: this is where the real transformation is happening. I.e. the Resources for the target platform get created such as docker images, manifests...

        Exceptions have to be handled within the method, The transformation will abort if a runtime exception gets thrown out of the method. To abort the transformation yo have to execute throw new RuntimeException()

      • cleanup

        public void cleanup()
        Description copied from interface: TransformationLifecycle
        Has to implement the clean (cleanup) lifecycle operations

        Exceptions within this operation have to get caught in order to prevent failure of the transformation
